race.comment: The $5 million King Charles III Stakes promises another thrilling showdown. FANGIRL (10) was back near her best last start, edging out the red-hot Lindermann and looking ready to peak. She won this race two years ago and, despite a tricky draw, will relish the tempo POJ sets and can storm home late. TOM KITTEN (5) was a forgive run first-up in the farcical Makybe Diva, then left chasing shadows at the Valley. From a middle draw, he finally gets his chance to strike if close enough turning in. PRIDE OF JENNI (11) blitzed them fresh in the Feehan and won't change her tactics. If no one takes her on, she could simply run them off their feet again. MR BRIGHTSIDE (1) capitalised on a soft lead last time but won't get that luxury here. Still, he's as tough as they come and chasing a remarkable 11th G1 win. PERICLES (6) is flying this prep, drawn perfectly, and should be in the thick of it throughout.
